            <span class="offer-highlight">As a token of our appreciation, complete the survey and enter our draw for a chance to WIN a [e.g., $100 Gift Card]!</span>
            <p>Your feedback is invaluable in helping us serve you better.</p>
            <a href="[YOUR_SURVEY_LINK_HERE]" class="cta-button">Take the Survey Now</a>
        </div>
        <div class="gift-section">
            <h3>Win Big!</h3>
            <p>Don't miss out on this opportunity to share your thoughts and potentially win an amazing prize. The survey will only take a few minutes!</p>
        </div>
        <div class="footer">
            <p>&copy; 2023 [Your Company Name]. All rights reserved.</p>
            <p>[Your Company Address] | <a href="[UNSUBSCRIBE_LINK_HERE]">Unsubscribe</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

**Explanation and How to Use:**

1.  **`<!DOCTYPE html>` and `<html>`:** Standard HTML document structure.
2.  **`<head>`:**
    *   **`<meta charset="UTF-8">`:** Ensures proper character encoding.
    *   **`<meta name="viewport" ...>`:** Makes the email responsive on different devices.
    *   **`<title>`:** The title that appears in the browser tab (less relevant for emails but good practice).
    *   **`<style>`:** This is where all the CSS styling is embedded.
        *   **`body`:** Sets a clean, modern font, removes default margins, and adds a light background color.
        *   **`.email-container`:** The main wrapper for the email content. It's centered, has a max-width, a white background, rounded corners, and a subtle shadow for depth.
        *   **`.header`:** The top section of the email. It features a vibrant green background, white text, and a prominent heading and subheading.
        *   **`.header h1`, `.header p`:** Styling for the text within the header.
        *   **`.content`:** The main body of the email. Includes padding, centered text, and styling for headings and paragraphs.
        *   **`.content h2`, `.content p`:** Styling for the main message.
        *   **`.offer-highlight`:** A distinct style for the key promotional message, making it stand out with a bold font and an amber color.
        *   **`.cta-button`:** The call-to-action button. It's styled with a bright orange background, white text, rounded corners, and a hover effect for interactivity. `color: #ffffff !important;` is crucial to ensure the link color doesn't get overridden by default email client link styles.
        *   **`.cta-button:hover`:** Changes the button color slightly when the mouse hovers over it.
        *   **`.gift-section`:** A distinct section highlighting the prize, using a light green background and clear headings/text.
        *   **`.gift-section h3`, `.gift-section p`:** Styling for the gift announcement.
        *   **`.footer`:** The bottom section of the email, containing copyright, address, and an unsubscribe link. It uses a muted gray color and smaller font size.
        *   **`.footer a`:** Styles the links in the footer.

3.  **`<body>`:**
    *   **`<div class="email-container">`:** Wraps all the email content.
    *   **`<div class="header">`:** Contains the main heading and a catchy subheading.
    *   **`<div class="content">`:** Holds the main message, the offer highlight, and the call-to-action button.
    *   **`<span class="offer-highlight">`:** Used to specifically style the promotional offer text.
    *   **`<a href="[YOUR_SURVEY_LINK_HERE]" class="cta-button">`:** **This is your main Call to Action button.**
        *   **Replace `[YOUR_SURVEY_LINK_HERE]` with the actual URL to your survey.**
    *   **`<div class="gift-section">`:** Details
